                <h1>All Saints' Day: Honoring Saints Worldwide</h1>
                <p>All Saints' Day, celebrated on November 1st, honors all saints, known and unknown. It originated in the early Christian Church as a day for believers to remember those who have triumphed in faith. Traditions vary worldwide, featuring church services, feasts, and festivities, creating a vibrant atmosphere of remembrance and gratitude.</p>
